    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix RLF synchronization handling to prevent NGAP interface errors\n\n### Summary\nThe RLF synchronization handling in the NR UE RRC stack was not compliant with 3GPP specifications, causing NGAP interface errors between gNB and AMF during radio link failure detection procedures.\n\nThe issue occurred when the UE received out-of-sync indications from lower layers. The previous implementation had overly restrictive timer checks that prevented proper N310 counter incrementing, leading to incorrect T310 timer management and subsequent NGAP procedure failures.\n\nThis fix reorders the RLF handling logic to be compliant with 3GPP 38.331 section 5.3.10.3, ensuring that N310 is incremented regardless of other timer states and that T310 is only started when not already running.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_timers_and_constants.c`: Modified `handle_rlf_sync` function to properly handle synchronization indications according to 3GPP specifications.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE to connect to a gNB with RRC connection\n2. Force radio link failure conditions (e.g., by attenuating signal)\n3. Observe that the UE fails to properly detect RLF conditions\n4. Check gNB logs for NGAP interface errors related to UE context release\n5. Monitor that T310 timer is not started correctly when out-of-sync indications are received\n\nThe fix ensures proper RLF detection and prevents downstream NGAP interface handling errors between gNB and AMF.\n"
}